    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0013"/>
        		<head>Jim to ? <date value="04-15">Apr’15</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
        			<dateline><date value="04-15">Apr’15</date></dateline>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            Just a little farewell line.  We are to be gone a long time; maybe three months.  Fortunately I am in the 
            most lucky squad for we are being taken in as soldiers and are to work with the French ambulances right on 
            the line.  Our base is between Nancy and the front where we will be able to do some real work.		
            I can’t thank you too much for your dear note.  That I will take with me, but you 
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0014" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            must supplement it with others.  You will won’t you?  And tho [sic] I may be gone a long time you won’t 
            forget Havre; the walks in the Bois, &mdash; and that you are everything to me over here &mdash; or elsewhere for that matter.			
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>My most sincere compliments to your dear family, and my deepest affection.</salute>
        		
        		<signed>Jim</signed>
        		       		
            <seg type="postscript">
            Address me here until I can let you know my new address.
            
            We have a review by the Minister of War at 4:30 and then we’re off, traveling all night this date.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0015"/>
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0016"/>
        		
            </div1>
           </body>
    </text>
